You are an independent adversarial auditor running PASS 5 (convergence confirmation) on /Users/[REDACTED]/hc-assay (branch main) after FOUR prior fix passes resolved 27 findings. READ-ONLY: no edits, no git mutation, no gh. You may read files and run /Users/[REDACTED]/hc-assay/.venv/bin/python, pytest, ruff, mypy.

This is a convergence gate: determine whether any REAL defect remains. Prior passes have heavily covered firewalls, the confirm machinery (direction-aware p, engine-measured stability, validation), _frozen.py (deep immutability/hashability incl. leaf/array/nested edge cases), fence.py (value-payload freezing + recursive interpretation rejection), schema/contract validation, registry locking, phase/gate mode-awareness, hypothesis lock/direction binding, stub fail-loud, packaging/CI.

Hold a HIGH bar. Report ONLY genuine defects (correctness, methodology-fidelity, contract-integrity, security) with a concrete repro or precise evidence. Explicitly do NOT report style nits, formatting, or already-fixed issues. Look especially for things four waves could have collectively overlooked:
- subtle cross-module/runtime-integration bugs;
- any remaining path to a wrong/incoherent Verdict, a firewall bypass, or dataset-specifics leaking into the engine;
- docstring/doc claims that still overstate what the code enforces;
- untested critical branches that hide a bug.

Run the full suite (ruff/mypy/pytest) and report status.

If genuine defects remain: FINDING N — TITLE / SEVERITY / LOCATION / CLAIM / EVIDENCE / SUGGESTED FIX.
If the engine has converged: output exactly `NO FINDINGS` followed by a concise list of what you checked and confirmed clean. Do not invent issues to seem productive; a clean convergence result is the correct and expected outcome if the code is sound.
